Detailed Description

Interface toward europa.

This class connects to europa components manipulated by TREX

Author:
Conor Mcgann & Frederic Py <fpy@mbari.org>

bool Assembly::isInternal ( EUROPA::ObjectId const &  obj  )  const

Check if internal.

Parameters:
[in] obj An object

Check if obj is a trex Internal timeline.

Note:
This checkinfg is at the reactor level -- and not simply ate the model level. Indeed, it may happen that a timeline has been specified as Internal by the model but was already owned by another reactor. In that case a warning message would have been displayed in TREX.log and this timeline mode would have been set as Private and this method will return false
Bug:
I am not sure that this policy to migrate a timline from Internal o Private is the good one. It may be better to demote failed Internal timelines to External until we can take ownership of this timeline ...
Return values:
true if obj is a trex Internal timeline
false otherwise
See also:
isExternal(EUROPA::ObjectId const &) const
isIgnored(EUROPA::ObjectId const &) const

Load a model.

Get trex timelines.

Symbol const Assembly::IGNORE_MODE [static]

Europa ignored timelines descriptor.

The value used to specify that a specific timeline is ignored by the model

Deprecated:
This kind of timleine was used in the past when all europa reactors were loading the same model. As we now have each reactor loading their own model such feature is not really useful and may disappear in future versions

Europa private timelines descriptor.

The value used to specify a timeline as private in an nddl model. Private timelines are TREX timelines that are not shared with other reactors. They behave like regular europa timelines
